  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_2' aria-label=\" Vijay Kumar versus Central Bank of India & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('2','2025','2025_7_523_533','2025INSC848'); ><font size='4'> <strong>VIJAY KUMAR<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>CENTRAL BANK OF INDIA & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 7 S.C.R. 523</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 848</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010002892025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : PAMIDIGHANTAM SRI NARASIMHA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, JOYMALYA BAGCHI</strong><br> Issue for Consideration The High Court upheld reduction of one-third of the pension payable to the appellant under the Central Bank of India (Employees&rsquo;) Pension Regulations, 1995. Headnotes&dagger; Central Bank of India (Employees&rsquo;) Pension Regulations, 1995 &ndash; Central Bank of 1979 &ndash; Central Bank of India Officer Employees&rsquo; (Discipline and Appeal) Regulations, 1976 &ndash; Allegation against the appellant that he sanctioned loans without proper appraisal &ndash; Inquiry was initiated &ndash; Inquiry report held the appellant guilty &ndash; Consequent<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 15-07-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 9496/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Case Allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('2','2025','2025_7_523_533','2025INSC848','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-aut